transfers_efl['year'] = pd.to_numeric(transfers_efl['year'], errors='coerce')

# Filter rows within the relevant timeframe (2012 to 2021)
transfers_efl = transfers_efl[(transfers_efl['year'] >= 2012) & (transfers_efl['year'] < 2021)]

transfers_efl['fee'] = transfers_efl['fee'].astype(str)

# Replace non-numeric values with zeros
non_numeric_values = ['?', '-', 'loan transfer', 'free transfer']

def clean_fee(value):
    if value in non_numeric_values or re.match(r'^End of loan', value):
        return 0
    return value

transfers_efl['fee'] = transfers_efl['fee'].apply(clean_fee)

# Convert monetary values to numerical form
def convert_monetary_value(value):
    if isinstance(value, str) and re.match(r'^€', value):
        if re.match(r'^€\d+\.\d+m$', value):
            return int(float(value[1:-1]) * 1000000)
        elif re.match(r'^€\d+Th\.$', value):
            return int(float(value[1:-3]) * 1000)
    if isinstance(value, str) and re.match(r'^Loan fee:€', value):
        if re.match(r'^Loan fee:€\d+\.\d+m$', value):
            return int(float(value[10:-1]) * 1000000)
        elif re.match(r'^Loan fee:€\d+Th\.$', value):
            return int(float(value[10:-3]) * 1000)
    return value

transfers_efl['fee'] = transfers_efl['fee'].apply(convert_monetary_value)

def sum_fees(values):
    return sum(int(value) for value in values if pd.notna(value) and str(value).isdigit())

summary_df = transfers_efl.groupby(['club_name', 'year', 'transfer_movement'])['fee'].apply(sum_fees).unstack(fill_value=0)


# Rename columns for clarity
summary_df.rename(columns={'in': 'value_spent', 'out': 'total_sold'}, inplace=True)

summary_df['net_value'] = summary_df['total_sold'] - summary_df['value_spent']

# Reset the index to get club_name and year as columns
summary_df.reset_index(inplace=True)
